window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>They're not just going to share me. They're going to make me call them both daddy.</b></p> <p>Connor Murphy was the perfect husband for a bratva kingpin's daughter. An Irish mafia boss I could marry to secure an alliance between our families. It was all supposed to be so simple...</p> <p>But then our wedding was attacked and I ended up on the run with his brother Caden.</p> <p>Now I'm caught between two men, and I can't tell which way is what.</p> <p>Not when Caden takes me over his knee, and definitely not when Connor bends me over and bares my bright red ass with his brother watching before making me come so hard I pass out.</p> <p>But the most shameful part isn't them spanking me, or sharing me, or even them making me beg before they claim me both at once, filling me completely while I writhe and scream and climax.</p> <p>It's calling them both daddy while they do all of that.</p> <p>Share Me, Daddy <i>is a standalone novel and is the fifth book of the Boston Kings series. For mature listeners.</i></p>"; 
